section.product--genome#genome
  .content
    img.product-icon src="/images/genome-icon.png" alt="Genome logo" width="64"
    h2.product-title Genome
    p.product-summary Yet another node task runner.
    p Simple library for compiling your front-end files. There's no messy configuration
      like with Grunt and no awkward conventions like with Gulp. No plugins required to
      get your favorite precompilers to work. Just write plain Javascript. You can handle
      files using streams, promises or plain strings. However your precompiler works,
      Genome can handle it.
    p.product-links
      a.product-link href="https://www.npmjs.com/package/genome" event-category="Genome" event-action="click" event-label="NPM"
        img src="/images/npm.png" alt="View at npm" width="100" style="margin-top:5px"
      a.product-link href="https://github.com/jpsilva/genome" event-category="Genome" event-action="click" event-label="GitHub"
        img src="/images/github.png" alt="Clone from GitHub" width="100"
section.product--serva#serva
  .content
    h2.product-title Serva for Atom.io
    p.product-summary Run a static web server from any directory in your project.
    p.product-summary
      a.repo-links href="https://travis-ci.org/jpsilva/serva": img src="https://travis-ci.org/jpsilva/serva.svg?branch=master" alt="Build Status"
      a.repo-links href="https://atom.io/packages/serva": img src="https://img.shields.io/apm/dm/serva.svg" alt="apm"
      a.repo-links href="https://atom.io/packages/serva": img src="https://img.shields.io/apm/v/serva.svg" alt="apm"
    p There are many static server packages for Atom, but for some reason, none seem to work. Even if they did, they don't have the flexibility I'm looking for. This package requires no setup and doesn't assume that you want to serve from just the root of your project.
    p Just right click on any directory in the tree view in Atom and choose "Serva > Start Server" to instantly start a static web server in that directory. It's that easy. It will even watch your files for changes and reload the server automatically.
    p.product-links
      a.product-link href="https://atom.io/packages/serva" event-category="serva" event-action="click" event-label="apm"
        img src="https://cloud.githubusercontent.com/assets/72919/2874231/3af1db48-d3dd-11e3-98dc-6066f8bc766f.png" alt="Serva's Atom package manager page" width="150" style="margin-top:5px"
      a.product-link href="https://github.com/jpsilva/serva" event-category="slm-autocompile" event-action="click" event-label="GitHub"
        img src="/images/github.png" alt="Clone serva from GitHub" width="100"

section.product--slm-autocompile#slm-autocompile
  .content
    h2.product-title Slm Autocompile for Atom.io
    p.product-summary Auto compile Slm files on save.
    p.product-summary
      a.repo-links href="https://travis-ci.org/jpsilva/slm-autocompile": img src="https://travis-ci.org/jpsilva/slm-autocompile.svg?branch=master" alt="Build Status"
      a.repo-links href="https://atom.io/packages/slm-autocompile": img src="https://img.shields.io/apm/dm/slm-autocompile.svg" alt="apm"
      a.repo-links href="https://atom.io/packages/slm-autocompile": img src="https://img.shields.io/apm/v/slm-autocompile.svg" alt="apm"
    p
      . Despite it's lack of documentation for advanced features,
      a href="https://github.com/slm-lang/slm" Slm
      |  is my favorite HTML preprocessor. It's better than HAML, Jade and Slim. It's what
        I use to build this website. So I thought I'd make this easy templating language
        even easier to use.
    p.product-links
      a.product-link href="https://atom.io/packages/slm-autocompile" event-category="slm-autocompile" event-action="click" event-label="apm"
        img src="https://cloud.githubusercontent.com/assets/72919/2874231/3af1db48-d3dd-11e3-98dc-6066f8bc766f.png" alt="slm-autocomplete's Atom package manager page" width="150" style="margin-top:5px"
      a.product-link href="https://github.com/jpsilva/slm-autocompile" event-category="slm-autocompile" event-action="click" event-label="GitHub"
        img src="/images/github.png" alt="Clone slm-autocomplete from GitHub" width="100"
